---
import { ceoPayData, homeownershipData, mobileData } from "../../data/charts";
import BarChart from "../charts/BarChart.astro";
import LaborChart from "../charts/LaborChart.astro";
import TreemapChart from "../charts/TreemapChart.astro";
import StatNumber from "../StatNumber.astro";
---

<section id="labor" aria-labelledby="labor-heading">
	<div class="two-col labor-layout">
		<div class="col-text">
			<div class="section-label reveal-left">Labour, Housing &amp; Land</div>
			<h2 id="labor-heading" class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.1s">
				Workers Produce.<br />Capital Captures.
			</h2>
			<p>
				South Africa's labour story begins in the mines. The compound
				system, influx control, and the migrant labour network were not
				incidental to apartheid — they were its engine, built to
				deliver a captive workforce to British and Afrikaner capital. The
				1994 transition brought formal labour rights, but the underlying
				structure of who owns what and who works for whom was left
				unchanged. GEAR (1996) imposed wage "flexibility" in service of
				investor confidence. Labour broking exploded. Casualisation spread.
				And on 16 August 2012, at Marikana, 34 striking platinum
				mineworkers were shot dead by police — making plain that
				post-apartheid South Africa's state would protect capital with the
				same methods as its predecessor.
			</p>
			<div class="stat-grid reveal">
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-housing-0">
					<StatNumber target={32.9} suffix="%" />
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-housing-0">
						Formal unemployment rate — 41.9% under the expanded
						definition. The majority of the unemployed are Black African
						women under 35<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: Stats SA QLFS Q1 2024" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="Statistics South Africa, Quarterly Labour Force Survey Q1 2024" data-url="https://www.statssa.gov.za/?page_id=1854&PPN=P0211">*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-housing-1">
					<StatNumber target={541} suffix=":1" />
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-housing-1">
						CEO-to-median-worker pay ratio at JSE-listed companies in
						2022 — up from approximately 85:1 in 1994<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: PwC Executive Trends SA 2023" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="PwC, Executive Directors: Practices and Remuneration Trends 2023" data-url="https://www.pwc.co.za/en/publications/executive-directors-practices-and-remuneration-trends.html">*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-housing-2">
					<StatNumber target={2.4} suffix="M" />
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-housing-2">
						Housing backlog — the number of households without adequate
						formal housing. Larger than in 1994 despite 30 years of
						delivery<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: Department of Human Settlements 2023" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="South Africa Department of Human Settlements, Annual Report 2023/24" data-url="https://www.dhs.gov.za/content/annual-reports">*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-housing-3">
					<StatNumber target={393} prefix="$" suffix="T" />
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-housing-3">
						Global real estate value — the largest asset class on earth<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: Savills 2024" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="Savills, How Much Is Global Real Estate Worth?, 2024" data-url="https://impacts.savills.com/market-trends/how-much-is-global-real-estate-worth.html">*</button>.
						In South Africa, commercial farmland remains concentrated in
						fewer than 40,000 farms, the vast majority white-owned
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="pull-quote reveal">
				<blockquote>
					"The post-apartheid state has not broken with the
					minerals-energy complex. It has been incorporated into it."
				</blockquote>
				<cite>— Patrick Bond, <em>Elite Transition</em>, 2000</cite>
			</div>
			<p class="source">
				Source:
				<a href="https://www.statssa.gov.za" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Statistics South Africa</a> ·
				<a href="https://www.pwc.co.za" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PwC Executive Trends SA</a> ·
				<a href="https://www.ilo.org/global/research/global-reports/weso/lang--en/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ILO World Employment and Social Outlook 2024</a> ·
				<a href="https://www.dhs.gov.za" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Department of Human Settlements</a>
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="col-charts">
			<figure class="chart-box reveal">
				<figcaption class="chart-title">Labour vs Capital Share of GDP — South Africa</figcaption>
				<div id="labor-desktop-chart" class="desktop-chart" role="img" aria-label="Area chart showing South Africa's labour share of GDP falling from 55% in 1990 to 46% in 2025, with capital share rising from 45% to 54%. The 1996 GEAR policy marks the inflection point.">
					<LaborChart />
				</div>
				<div id="labor-mobile-chart" class="mobile-chart" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart showing South African labour vs capital share of GDP">
					<BarChart id="labor-mobile-bars" items={mobileData.labor} />
				</div>
				<table class="sr-only">
					<caption>Labour vs Capital Share of GDP — South Africa</caption>
					<thead><tr><th>Year</th><th>Labour</th><th>Capital</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>1990</td><td>55%</td><td>45%</td></tr>
						<tr><td>1994</td><td>54%</td><td>46%</td></tr>
						<tr><td>2008</td><td>51%</td><td>49%</td></tr>
						<tr><td>2025</td><td>46%</td><td>54%</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</figure>
			<figure class="chart-box reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.12s">
				<figcaption class="chart-title">
					CEO-to-Worker Pay Ratio — JSE-listed Companies&nbsp;<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: PwC Executive Trends SA 2023" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="PwC, Executive Directors: Practices and Remuneration Trends 2023" data-url="https://www.pwc.co.za/en/publications/executive-directors-practices-and-remuneration-trends.html">*</button>
				</figcaption>
				<div role="img" aria-label="CEO-to-worker pay ratio at JSE-listed companies (PwC SA): 1994: approximately 85:1, 2005: approximately 200:1, 2015: approximately 400:1, 2022: 541:1">
					<BarChart id="ceo-pay-chart" items={ceoPayData} outsideValueThreshold={20} />
				</div>
			</figure>
			<figure class="chart-box reveal">
				<figcaption class="chart-title">
					SA Housing Backlog — Units Required&nbsp;<button type="button" class="cite-ref" aria-label="View source: Department of Human Settlements" aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false" data-source="South Africa Department of Human Settlements, Annual Report 2023/24" data-url="https://www.dhs.gov.za/content/annual-reports">*</button>
				</figcaption>
				<div role="img" aria-label="Bar chart showing the South African housing backlog growing from approximately 1.5 million units in 1994 to 2.4 million units in 2024, despite 30 years of post-apartheid housing delivery">
					<BarChart id="homeownership-chart" items={homeownershipData} outsideValueThreshold={5} />
				</div>
			</figure>
			<figure class="chart-box reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.12s">
				<figcaption class="chart-title">Global Asset Classes by Value</figcaption>
				<div id="asset-treemap-desktop-chart" class="desktop-chart" role="img" aria-label="Treemap showing global asset classes by value: Real estate dominates at $393 trillion">
					<TreemapChart />
				</div>
				<div id="asset-treemap-mobile-chart" class="mobile-chart" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart showing global asset classes by value">
					<BarChart id="treemap-mobile-bars" items={mobileData.treemap} outsideValueThreshold={5} />
				</div>
				<table class="sr-only">
					<caption>Global Asset Classes by Value</caption>
					<thead><tr><th>Asset Class</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>Real Estate</td><td>$393T</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Equities</td><td>$109T</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Government Debt</td><td>$66T</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Gold</td><td>$14T</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</figure>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
